'''Pog''' lived on [[Tralus/Legends|Tralus]] and was a member of the fringe community.

Pog had access to the elite [[Cynabar's InfoNet]], and in [[6 BBY/Legends|29:3:3]], advertised the use of the [[ThunderForce]] mercenary group, who had previously won the [[Battle of Binquaros]]. As their agent, Pog offered to meet any prospective employers at [[Fathoms]] on [[Dac/Legends|Mon Calamari]], and give them a tour of the mercenaries' [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] facilities if necessary.<ref name="has">''[[Hideouts & Strongholds]]''</ref>

Later in [[1 ABY/Legends|36:3:1]], Pog responded to a post by the [[TriNebulon News/Legends|TriNebulon News]] reporter [[Andor Javin]]. Javin claimed that the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] was behind a conspiracy that caused the [[IG-88 assassin droid/Legends|IG-88]] series to kill their designers. Pog called Javin a "conspiracy buff" and disputed the rationality of his theory.<ref name="cft">''[[Cynabar's Fantastic Technology: Droids]]''</ref>

